      "content": "i get the resistance thing but it just feels like so much unnecessary stuff going into my body when the problem is literally gone. my friend said that if the bacteria are dead, the medicine isn't doing anything anymore and it's just taxing my liver for no reason. do you actually know for sure that i'll get sick again if i stop now? it feels like doctors just prescribe long courses to be safe, but is it actually medically required at this point?",
